kes over and over again.  People don't retell stories of slavery and the Holocaust because they make neat campfire stories.  They tell them so future generations could learn from these mistakes.  I have no doubt that someday scientists will locate the gene that proves homosexuality is not a &quot;choice&quot;.  When this happens, then society will change its tune.  Some people say they don't like homosexual behavior because it is too hard to explain it to their kids.  Well, I say bring it on.  Let my son see two men holding hands in public so I can start the education process.  Education is the key to eliminating discrimination and bigotry in all its forms.  We can't educate our children if we are hiding those that are different behind closed doors and away from our schools and public emporiums.  <br>
